Residents of Bungoma county who have attained the age of 18 or lost their identity cards have been advised to apply for the documents as they await Huduma cards. Bungoma registration officer Scholastica Arucho said the county has so far received 64,812 Huduma cards. She said the collection of Huduma cards in the county is at 74.65 per cent. Arucho said 9,478 IDs remain uncollected in their office and at the Huduma centre. She urged residents to collect their identity cards once they have been processed. Arucho said many residents have stopped applying for identity cards because they are waiting for Huduma cards. She advised residents that they cannot apply for Huduma cards without identity cards.  Edited by A.N  